&gt; that you don&#39;t worry about it.  All webservers have the defaults semantics
&gt; built in when a link is requested that is no longer exists it returns a 404.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; If a service is much more robust, accessing a dead link would redirect it
&gt; to something meaningful, maybe a the &quot;top&quot; of the app or the &quot;top&quot; of the
&gt; entity.  This is optional and requires some more thought in how you
&gt; implement your service but may be worth its weight in gold when you need to
&gt; upgrade.
&gt;
&gt; It is worth exploring more, in my opinion.
&gt;
&gt; -Noah
